title.narrative: ACCESS TO Water, Sanitation, and Hygiene (WASH) FACILITIES

description.narrative: Facilities for safe drinking water and adequate sanitation are available to vulnerable people in the target areas, which contributes to Children In Urban Settings / Local Governance, Disaster Risk Reduction, Environmental Sustainability, Environmental Sustainability (Covid), Sanitation, Water. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Harnessing Power Of Business And Markets, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Children and women in vulnerable regions use drinking water points and sanitation facilities and adopt good hygiene practices, including in emergency situations.

title.narrative: Facilities for safe drinking water and adequate sanitation are available to vulnerable people in the target areas

description.narrative: Access to safe drinking water at the national level has slightly progressed from 65.39% to 65.72% at the national level and the proportion of health care facilities with functional water and sanitation services is estimated at 51% (UNICEF 2021 Assessment). Even though the progress has been slow, UNICEF has contributed with 3,5000 people that have gained access to safe drinking water services in 2021.; Hundred (100) schools have been provided with aces to water, sanitation and or handwashing facility. | Status:Met | As-of Date:01/02/2022
